text:
I love the boston dynamics videos, but I am constantly wondering how robust these things are under changes to their environment.  If I can just write a script like
```moveto(tall_robot, boxes)
unpack(tall_robot, boxes)
pickup(tall_robot, robot_dog)```
than wow :mind_blown: this is so awesome.  If I have to right 30 k lines of code to handle  the box being moved 1 mm to the left, or the atmospheric pressure being half a pascal too high, or cosmic rays, or astological signs, then it's not really that exciting
